                            <h1>
                            By Faith All Things Are Fulfilled
                            </h1>
                            <h2 class="author">
                                    <a href="http://www.lds.org/church/leader/marcus-b-nash?lang=eng"><div class="byline" id="">
					<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p2" class="">By Elder Marcus&nbsp;B. Nash</p>
					<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p3" class="">Of the Seventy</p>
				</div></a>   
                                    </h2>
                            <hr>
                        </div><!-- end #details -->
                       
                        <div id="primary">
                            
                            <div class="audio-player">
                                        <div id="audioClose"><a href="#" title="Close Audio" onclick="closeAudioPlayer(); return false;">Close Audio</a></div>
                                    </div>
                            <blockquote class="intro dontHighlight">
                                        <a href="http://www.lds.org/church/leader/marcus-b-nash?lang=eng">
                                                        <img id="talkPhoto" src="/bc/content/shared/content/images/leaders/marcus-b-nash-10.jpg" alt="Marcus B. Nash" class="img-decor">
                                                    </a>
                                        
                                        <div class="kicker" id="">Faith will help us to safely climb the gospel path, overcome every challenge of mortality, and return to the majestic presence of our Heavenly Father.</div>
                                        
                                    </blockquote>
                            
                            <span style="display: none" id="article-id">10411_000_038</span>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p5" class="">Not long ago several of us in the Nash <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/ensign/2003/05/the-importance-of-the-family?lang=eng">family</a> hiked to the top of Huayna Picchu, a tall peak adjoining the ancient Incan ruins of Machu Picchu in the mountains of Peru. It is a very steep climb with breathtaking views and precipitous drop-offs. Sadly, some hikers have lost their lives by falling off that narrow, steep trail. To avoid such tragedies, strong cables have since been secured to the solid rock along the mountainside of Huayna Picchu. We held to those cables as we climbed, and they enabled us to safely reach the summit, where the view was majestic!</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p6" class="">Like the path on Huayna Picchu, our mortal journey is a steep and difficult climb, one that requires our Heavenly Father&rsquo;s help to successfully complete. For this reason, He established the principles and ordinances of the gospel to bring us unto the Savior and His saving power.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote1-10411_000_038">1</a></sup> The first of those principles, faith in the Lord <a class="no-link-style" href="http://mormon.org/jesus-christ">Jesus Christ</a>,<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote2-10411_000_038">2</a></sup> is like the cables on Huayna Picchu: if strong and securely attached to &ldquo;the rock of our Redeemer,&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote3-10411_000_038">3</a></sup> faith will help us to safely climb the gospel path, overcome every challenge of mortality,<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote4-10411_000_038">4</a></sup> and return to the majestic presence of our Heavenly Father. All things are fulfilled by faith.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote5-10411_000_038">5</a></sup></p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p7" class="">Faith is both a principle of action and of power.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote6-10411_000_038">6</a></sup> It &ldquo;is not to have a perfect knowledge of things; therefore if [we] have faith [we] hope for things which are not seen, which are true.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote7-10411_000_038">7</a></sup> It is an assurance<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote8-10411_000_038">8</a></sup> of the Spirit gained through our learning that moves us to act<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote9-10411_000_038">9</a></sup> to follow the example of the Savior and prayerfully keep His commandments, even through times of sacrifice and trial.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote10-10411_000_038">10</a></sup> Faith brings us the power of the Lord, which&mdash;among other things&mdash;is manifested by a hope of good things to come,<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote11-10411_000_038">11</a></sup> miracles that confirm our faith,<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote12-10411_000_038">12</a></sup> and divine protection in spiritual and temporal matters.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote13-10411_000_038">13</a></sup></p>
				<span class="story">
					<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p8" class="">The life of Ann Rowley, a pioneer woman in the early days of the Church, demonstrates how exercising faith impacts our lives for good. A widow from England, Sister Rowley exercised her faith to answer the prophet&rsquo;s call to gather to Zion. She was a member of the Willie handcart company, which encountered deep snowdrifts along the trail in the fall of 1856. They had reached a point in the trek where her seven children were literally starving. She wrote: &ldquo;It hurt me to see my children go hungry. &hellip; Night was coming and there was no food for the evening meal. I asked God&rsquo;s help as I always did. I got on my knees, remembering two hard sea biscuits that &hellip; had been left over from the sea voyage. They were not large, and were so hard they couldn&rsquo;t be broken. Surely, that was not enough to feed 8 people, but 5 loaves and 2 fishes were not enough to feed 5,000 people either, but through a miracle, Jesus had done it. So, with God&rsquo;s help, nothing is impossible. I found the biscuits and put them in a dutch oven and covered them with water and asked for God&rsquo;s blessing. Then I put the lid on the pan and set it on the coals. When I took off the lid a little later, I found the pan filled with food. I kneeled with my family and thanked God for his goodness. That night my family had sufficient food.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote14-10411_000_038">14</a></sup></p>
				</span>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p9" class="">Ann Rowley was living the gospel at great personal sacrifice. She needed help and asked for it in prayer. Because of her faith, she was filled with hope and miraculously provided with food for her family. The Lord also blessed her with the eternally significant ability to &ldquo;endure in faith to the end.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote15-10411_000_038">15</a></sup> Despite an uncertain future, she did not demand to know how she was going to feed her children the next day; instead, she patiently &ldquo;wait[ed] upon the Lord&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote16-10411_000_038">16</a></sup> and pressed forward with hope&mdash;just as the beautiful <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/cm/display/0,17631,4650-1,00.html">hymn</a> expresses:</p>
				<div class="figure">
					<div class="stanza" id="">
						<div class="line" id="">Lead, kindly Light, amid th&rsquo; encircling gloom; Lead thou me on!</div>
						<div class="line" id="">The night is dark, and I am far from home; Lead thou me on!</div>
						<div class="line" id="">Keep thou my feet; I do not ask to see</div>
						<div class="line" id="">The distant scene&mdash;one step enough for me.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote17-10411_000_038">17</a></sup></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p14" class="">We too can exercise such faith in the Lord, believing and trusting that our kind and constant God<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote18-10411_000_038">18</a></sup> will bless us with His miraculous power suited to our circumstance, according to His timing. As we do so, we too will see the hand of God manifest in our lives.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p15" class="">The Lord commands us to take &ldquo;the shield of faith wherewith ye shall be able to quench <span class="emphasis">all</span> the fiery darts of the wicked.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote19-10411_000_038">19</a></sup> Satan will use such things as doubt, fear, or sin to tempt us to let go of faith and lose the protection it offers. Let us briefly examine each of these challenges to faith in turn so that we can recognize and heed not the adversary&rsquo;s temptations.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote20-10411_000_038">20</a></sup></p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p16" class="">First, unbelief in the Lord or His gospel will cause us to resist the Spirit of God.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote21-10411_000_038">21</a></sup> The Lord&rsquo;s antidote for doubt is simple. As King Benjamin declared, &ldquo;Believe in God; believe that he is, and that he created all things, both in heaven and in earth; believe that he has all wisdom, and all power, both in heaven and in earth; believe that man doth not comprehend all the things which the Lord can comprehend.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote22-10411_000_038">22</a></sup></p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p17" class="">If, because of unbelief or doubt, you find your faith wavering, remember that even the ancient Apostles implored the Lord to &ldquo;increase our faith.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote23-10411_000_038">23</a></sup> Bearing in mind that faith and reason are necessary companions, consider the following analogy: faith and reason are like the two wings of an aircraft. Both are essential to maintain flight. If, from your perspective, reason seems to contradict faith, pause and remember that our perspective is extremely limited compared with the Lord&rsquo;s.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote24-10411_000_038">24</a></sup> Do not discard faith any more than you would detach a wing from an aircraft in flight. Instead, nurture a particle of faith and permit the hope it produces to be an anchor to your soul&mdash;and to your reason.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote25-10411_000_038">25</a></sup> That is why we are commanded to &ldquo;seek learning &hellip; by study <span class="emphasis">and also</span> by faith.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote26-10411_000_038">26</a></sup> Remember, faith precedes and produces miracles for which we have no immediate explanation within our experience, such as a Dutch oven full of food from two small biscuits or simply enduring in faith against all odds.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote27-10411_000_038">27</a></sup></p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p18" class="">Second, fear distracts from and undermines faith in the Savior. The Apostle Peter looked to the Lord one stormy night and walked on water&mdash;until he averted his gaze and &ldquo;saw the wind boisterous [and] was afraid&rdquo; and then sank into the stormy sea.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote28-10411_000_038">28</a></sup> He could have continued walking if he had not feared! Rather than our focusing upon and fearing the boisterous wind and waves in our lives, the Lord invites us to &ldquo;look unto me in every thought; doubt not, fear not.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote29-10411_000_038">29</a></sup></p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p19" class="">Third, sin diminishes the presence of the Spirit in our lives, and without the <a class="no-link-style" href="http://www.lds.org/study/topics/holy-ghost?lang=eng">Holy Ghost</a>, we will lack the spiritual stamina to hold onto and exercise faith. It is best to exercise our faith to &ldquo;touch not the evil gift, nor the unclean thing&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote30-10411_000_038">30</a></sup> and to &ldquo;be diligent in keeping all [the] commandments, lest &hellip; your faith fail you, and your enemies triumph over you.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote31-10411_000_038">31</a></sup> If sin has stained your life, I invite you to exercise &ldquo;faith unto repentance,&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote32-10411_000_038">32</a></sup> and the Savior, through the Atonement, will purify and heal your life.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p20" class="">Brothers and sisters, the Lord will, according to our faith, fulfill His promises and work with us to overcome every challenge.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote33-10411_000_038">33</a></sup> He did so for Ann Rowley and has done so for His people in all nations and in every age and generation. Because He is a &ldquo;God of miracles&rdquo; and &ldquo;changeth not,&rdquo; He will likewise bless each of us with hope, protection, and power according to our faith in Him.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote34-10411_000_038">34</a></sup> Steadfast faith in the Lord Jesus <a class="no-link-style" href="http://jesuschrist.lds.org/">Christ</a> will&mdash;like the cables on the path of Huayna Picchu&mdash;anchor you and your loved ones to &ldquo;the rock of our Redeemer&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote35-10411_000_038">35</a></sup> and His matchless power to save.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/2012/11/by-faith-all-things-are-fulfilled.p21" class="">President <a href="http://www.lds.org/church/leader/thomas-s-monson?lang=eng">Thomas&nbsp;S. Monson</a> has stated, &ldquo;The future is as bright as your faith.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote36-10411_000_038">36</a></sup> I testify of that sublime, hopeful truth and invite each of us to steadfastly press forward with faith in the Lord, &ldquo;nothing wavering.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote37-10411_000_038">37</a></sup> I know that the Savior lives, is &ldquo;the author and the finisher of [our] faith,&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote38-10411_000_038">38</a></sup> and the &ldquo;rewarder of them that diligently seek him.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#footnote39-10411_000_038">39</a></sup> I so testify in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.</p>
			
                            
                            
